public class TimeZoneFormat : Android.Icu.Text.UFormat, Android.Icu.Util.IFreezable, IDisposable

Docs.summary: TimeZoneFormat supports time zone display name formatting and parsing.

remarks.para: TimeZoneFormat supports time zone display name formatting and parsing. An instance of TimeZoneFormat works as a subformatter of SimpleDateFormat, but you can also directly get a new instance of TimeZoneFormat and formatting/parsing time zone display names.

ICU implements the time zone display names defined by UTS#35 Unicode Locale Data Markup Language (LDML). TimeZoneNames represents the time zone display name data model and this class implements the algorithm for actual formatting and parsing.

Docs.param: the offset from GMT(UTC) in milliseconds.
Docs.summary: Returns the localized GMT(UTC) offset format for the given offset.

remarks.para:
Returns the localized GMT(UTC) offset format for the given offset. The localized GMT offset is defined by;
  • GMT format pattern (e.g. "GMT {0}" - see #getGMTPattern())
  • Offset time pattern (e.g. "+HH:mm" - see #getGMTOffsetPattern(GMTOffsetPatternType))
  • Offset digits (e.g. "0123456789" - see #getGMTOffsetDigits())
  • GMT zero format (e.g. "GMT" - see #getGMTZeroFormat())
This format always uses 2 digit hours and minutes. When the given offset has non-zero seconds, 2 digit seconds field will be appended. For example, GMT+05:00 and GMT+05:28:06.
Portions of this page are modifications based on work created and shared by the Android Open Source Project and used according to terms described in the Creative Commons 2.5 Attribution License.

Docs.param: the offset from GMT(UTC) in milliseconds.
Docs.summary: Returns the short localized GMT(UTC) offset format for the given offset.
Docs.returns: the short localized GMT format string

remarks.para:
Returns the short localized GMT(UTC) offset format for the given offset. The short localized GMT offset is defined by;
  • GMT format pattern (e.g. "GMT {0}" - see #getGMTPattern())
  • Offset time pattern (e.g. "+HH:mm" - see #getGMTOffsetPattern(GMTOffsetPatternType))
  • Offset digits (e.g. "0123456789" - see #getGMTOffsetDigits())
  • GMT zero format (e.g. "GMT" - see #getGMTZeroFormat())
This format uses the shortest representation of offset. The hours field does not have leading zero and lower fields with zero will be truncated. For example, GMT+5 and GMT+530.
